The United States of America has been a very dominant country over the past years. This is because of the fact that the United States of America has a very strong military and a stable economy. It should be said that the United States of America gained independence from Britain in July of 1776. The incumbent president of the United States of America is Joe Biden. However, it should be said that there are some territories that are currently colonized by the United States of America. Let us carefully identify some of them.
1. Puerto Rico
The official name of this territory is the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico. It is located in North America. According to The Washington Post, Puerto Rico is currently under the colonial rule of the United States of America. According to a report by Britannica.com, Spain relinquished control of Puerto Rico to the United States of America after the Treaty of Paris was signed.
2. American Samoa
This is the second territory on this list. The American Samoa is located in the South Pacific Ocean. According to Britannica.com, this region is an unincorporated territory of the United States of America. According to the United States Department of the Interior, the American Samoa was ceded to the United States in 1900.


